import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='home_score', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['home_score'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['home_score'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['home_score'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['home_score'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of home scores?')
    plt.xlabel('Home Scores')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    data['count'] = 1
    data = data.groupby(['division']).sum().reset_index()
    sns.barplot(x='division', y='count', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of matches played by division?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Division')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Matches Played')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['result'] = 'Draw'
    data.loc[data['home_score'] > data['away_score'], 'result'] = 'Home Win'
    data.loc[data['home_score'] < data['away_score'], 'result'] = 'Away Win'
    result_counts = data['result'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(result_counts, labels=result_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of home wins, away wins, and draws?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
